accessrestrict.head: Restrictions on Access
accessrestrict.p: Student records in Series 1 are restricted for 100 years from date of record creation or until the death of the student. Access to student records is governed by the federal Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA), which protects the privacy of student education records.

userestrict.head: Restrictions on Use
userestrict.p: Some material may be copyrighted or restricted. It is the patron's obligation to determine and satisfy copyright or other case restrictions when publishing or otherwise distributing materials found in the collections.

bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: The Germanic Studies Department is today the German and Slavic Languages and Literatures Department.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Materials in this collection include budgets, departmental business, correspondence and reading exam results. The collection covers the years 1970 to 1995.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized in two series: Administrative records and Records.

accessrestrict.p: Access to student records is governed by the federal Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA), which protects the privacy of student education records. Student records are closed for 100 years from date of record creation.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series includes budgets, departmental business, correspondence, reading exam results and other administrative records from 1970-95.
